Package ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions

Contains all abstractions (base classes, interfaces).

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BiFunctionalI<T,U,R>  
    FunctionalI<T,R>  
    FunctionsI
    A common interface for functional operations on any Collection type.
    I<K,V>
    This interface type can be used as a convenience shorthand alias for ReadonlyIndexedI.
    IndexedI<K,V>
    An abstraction for a data structure with indexed (random) access.
    IndexedIFunctions<K,V>
    Adds a contract to work with functional interfaces to a IndexedI.
    IndexedIFunctionsS<K,V>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a IndexedIFunctions.
    IndexedIS<K,V>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a IndexedIFunctionsS.
    IndexedListI<K,V>
    Adds a contract to work with sequential access to a IndexedIS.
    IndexedListIS<K,V>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a IndexedListIAdd.
    OrderedSequential<T>
    Adds a contract for access to an ordered data structure to a SequentialIS.
    OrderedSequentialS<T>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a OrderedSequential.
    ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>
    An abstraction for a data structure with indexed (random) read-only access.
    SequentialI<T>
    An abstraction for a sequentially accessed data structure.
    SequentialIFunctions<T>
    Adds a contract to work with functional interfaces to a SequentialI.
    SequentialIFunctionsS<T>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a SequentialIFunctions.
    SequentialIS<T>
    Adds syntactic sugar to a SequentialIFunctionsS.
    StreamableI
    An abstraction for a streamable data structure.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    OmegaObject
    Base class for all instantiable classes.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IndexedListI.IndexAlreadyPresentException
    Signals that an attempt to IndexedListI.insert(Object, Object) an object with an already existing index / key has been detected and rejected.

Package ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions Description

Contains all abstractions (base classes, interfaces). You will typically rather work with the concrete implementations in the main package.
